ctual SMTP infrastructure. Mocked email delivery masks real failures: SMTP auth, connection timeout, server rejection, rate limiting, malformed headers.\n- MOCK-HIDE: A mocked email library always \"succeeds,\" hiding real mail server errors and delivery failures.\n- Minimum level: **System** (need real or test mail server to verify actual delivery)\n\n**Behavior 5: Email failure → save to file + retry next run**\n- REAL-INFRA: Filesystem behavior (permission errors, disk full, file I/O failures) and scheduled job execution (cron registration, actual retry trigger timing) are OS/infrastructure concerns.\n- MOCK-HIDE: Mocking filesystem and scheduler hides real failures: write fails silently, backup file unreadable, retry job never registered, file locking issues.\n- Minimum level: **System** (need real filesystem and scheduler to test complete retry flow)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13322,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13322},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ab8cb3b-ad49-43e9-80b1-7542def6bcad","uuid":"47e20a39-a681-428e-a121-793ff9f47d2d"}
